                            <comment id="21704" author="marthursson" created="Wed, 10 Jan 2007 04:17:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The postProcess() method will now be called regardless of what happens during the search, even if an exception is thrown from the search operation or from the iteration of the NamingEnumeration. If an exception occurs during postProcess() this will be translated and rethrown only if an exception wasn&apos;t previously encountered (in which the original exception will be used. PartialResultExceptions are still handled as before, i.e. they are only regarded as errors if &apos;ignorePartialResultException&apos; is set to false (the default).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
